15933d4c-4d19-4a1e-beb4-d27bd6fff4c9.04856216-0a22-4f7b-95b7-a00fdeec8e72.transition.description=${service} is manual 15933d4c-4d19-4a1e-beb4-d27bd6fff4c9.1e1d3823-803f-42a9-9660-918b0e29280b.transition.description=${service} is disabled. 15933d4c-4d19-4a1e-beb4-d27bd6fff4c9.1ec40bba-dbb1-44a9-8b4a-979f5f05d56a.prompt=Service Short Name\: 15933d4c-4d19-4a1e-beb4-d27bd6fff4c9.1fc2a7f3-bd26-4fc9-841f-53238144ec90.description=
Gets the start mode of a service.

Inputs\:
host - Hostname or ip address.
service - Service to query.
user - Username to use for WMI impersonation on the host for this operation (can be left blank).
password - Password of the user.

Responses\:
boot - Set to boot.
system - Set to system.
automatic - Set to auto.
manual - Set to manual.
disabled - Set to disabled.
automaticDelayedStart - Set to automatic delayed start.
failure - Failed to get startup mode.

Adds a value into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
